The username enumeration via hydra did not yield any valid user with the password 'invalidpassword' before I interrupted due to long execution.  
I will now try a different approach and check for weak or default credentials using commonly known username-password pairs for SSH servers running Go implementations. For that, I will try a set of common default pairs against this SSH service.  
I'll use hydra again with a preset small password list on the first few usernames from john.lst to keep this quick.  

I'll create a small username file with the first 5 usernames from john.lst and a small password file with some common defaults and try hydra again.  

Next, I create these username and password files and run hydra.

Now, I will create a small password list with some commonly used default or weak passwords to attempt with hydra. I'll create the file /tmp/passwords.txt with entries: password, 123456, admin, root, letmein, 1234.
I noticed the echo command to create the password file got cut off because I tried to send multi-line string directly. I will rewrite that command properly now to create the password file correctly.

I will run this with 4 threads and verbosity for monitoring.
